CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "PRODIGY ACCLAIMED - Talented 13-year-old Philippa Schuyler won acclaim from all of Pittsburgh's music critics when she thrilled a capacity audience in a piano recital at Schenley High School last Thursday. Here she accepts a bouquet from Yvonne Jackson. - Courier Photo by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Yvonne Jackson handing bouquet of flowers to Philippa Duke Schuyler, after piano recital in Schenley High School
